         <bibl xml:id="work-1406" ana="#hagiographic">
            <title xml:id="name1406-1"
                   xml:lang="syr"
                   source="#bib1406-1"
                   syriaca-tags="#syriaca-headword #syriaca-anglicized">ܘܟܣܝܡܘܣ</title>
            <title xml:id="name1406-2" xml:lang="fr-x-bhs" source="#bib1406-1">Maksīmōs</title>
            <title xml:id="name1406-3" xml:lang="fr" source="#bib1406-1">Maxime le Confesseur (texte)</title>
            <title xml:id="name1406-4"
                   xml:lang="en"
                   source="#bib1406-1"
                   syriaca-tags="#syriaca-headword #syriaca-anglicized">Maximus the Confessor (text)</title>
            <author xml:lang="fr" source="#bib1406-1">Georges de Resh ‘Ayna</author>
            <note xml:lang="syr" type="incipit" source="#bib1406-1">
               <quote>ܗܘ ܕܝܢ ܗܢܐ ܡܟܣܝܡܘܣ ܐܝܬܘܗܝ ܗܘܐ ܡܢ ܚܨܦܝܢ ܩܪܝܬܐ. ܬܡܢ ܓܝܪ ܐܬܝܠܕ ܗܘܐ. ܙܝܙܢܐ ܗܢܐ ܡܪܝܪܐ̣. ܐܒܘܗܝ ܓܝܪ ܫܡܪܝܐ ܗܘܐ ܡܢ ܫܟܪ̣. ܘܐܡܗ ܦܪܣܝܬܐ. ܘܐܝܬܝܗܿ ܗܘܬ ܐܡܬܗ ܕܓܒܪܐ ܚܕ ܝܗܘܕܝܐ. ܕܫܡܗ ܗܘܐ ܙܕܘܩ. ܡܢ ܛܝܒܝܪܝܐ ܡܕܝܢܬܐ.</quote>
            </note>
            <note xml:lang="fr" type="incipit" source="#bib1406-1">
               <quote>Ce Maxime était du village de Hesfîn, car c’est là que naquit cette mauvaise herbe amère; son père était Samaritain de Sichar et sa mère Persane, esclave d’un homme juif appelé Zadôq, de la ville de Tibériade.</quote>
            </note>
            <note type="editions">
               <bibl source="#bib1406-1">
                  <author>Brock, S.P.</author>
                  <title>An Early Syriac Life of Maximus the Confessor</title>
                  <citedRange>p. 302-313</citedRange>
               </bibl>
            </note>
            <note xml:lang="en" type="MSS" source="#bib1406-1">
               <bibl>ed: ms Londres, British Library, Rich. 7192, f. 72v-78v (mutilé de la fin)</bibl>
            </note>
            <note xml:lang="en" type="modernTranslation" source="#bib221-1">
               <bibl>S.P. Brock, p. 314-319</bibl>
            </note>
